@startuml
' @id(SEQ-VIEW-PUML-SOURCE)
' @ref(USE-VIEW-PUML-SOURCE)
'
' Objective-side flow for viewing a model file's raw PlantUML beside its
' rendered diagram. The Source toggle sits next to the Diagram and Diff
' toggles in the central panel; Source reads the .puml straight from disk
' and never invokes a renderer.
'
' @desc(SEQ-VIEW-PUML-SOURCE, "How clicking the Source toggle (next to Diagram) shows a model file's raw PlantUML: the viewer switches to View::Source, lazily reads the selected .puml text into SourceView (cached by path), and each frame paints it as scrollable read-only text with @id/@ref/@desc/@sec and @startuml/@enduml highlighted. Clicking Diagram repaints the rendered SVG; no renderer is invoked for Source.")
title View a model file's PlantUML source (objective)

actor "Developer" as Dev
participant "MddViewer\n(eframe::App)" as Viewer
participant "View\n{Svg|Source|Diff}" as Mode
participant "SourceView\n{loaded, source}" as SV
database ".mdd/models/<side>/\n<kind>/<name>.puml" as Puml
participant "DiagramPage\n(usvg/resvg) + paint_canvas" as Page

Dev -> Viewer : select a model file in the rail
Viewer -> Dev : show "Diagram | Source | Diff" toggle row (default Diagram)

alt toggle = Diagram (default)
  loop each painted frame
    Viewer -> Page : paint_canvas (rendered SVG, pan/zoom/fisheye)
    Page --> Dev : rendered diagram
  end
else toggle = Source
  Dev -> Viewer : click "Source"
  Viewer -> Mode : view = Source
  alt source not yet loaded for this path
    Viewer -> Puml : read raw text
    Puml --> SV : .puml source (cached by path)
  end
  loop each painted frame
    Viewer -> Dev : scrollable read-only text\n(@id / @ref / @desc / @sec and\n@startuml/@enduml highlighted)
  end
end

note over SV
  SourceView caches (loaded path, source text) so the
  file is read once per selection, then repainted each
  frame. Source depends on no rendered artifact — it is
  always self-sufficient (OCL-PUML-SOURCE-NO-RENDER),
  unlike the Diagram toggle which paints the pre-rendered
  SVG via DiagramPage.
end note
@enduml
